# qemu

	qemu -cdrom binary.iso

Qemu might be a little slow if you don't have the qemu kernel module running.

* [Archlinux Qemu guide](http://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Qemu)

## Testing the hard drive installer on ISO

Create the hard drive:

	qemu-img create test.qcow2 10G

Then try it out:

	wget http://build.webconverger.org/latest.iso
	qemu -kernel-kqemu -no-acpi -net nic,vlan=1 -net user,vlan=1 -hda test.qcow2 -cdrom webconverger.2009-09-06.5.5-iso.iso

**Issue** is getting network connectivity to analyse the debug logs.

## Testing the hard drive installer on [[USB]]

Create the hard drive:

	qemu-img create test.qcow2 10G

Then try it out:

	wget http://build.webconverger.org/latest.img
	qemu -hdb test.qcow2 webconverger.2009-09-06.5.5-usb.img


